@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@code{sync-journals-bib} walks a master BibTeX file, gathers the
unique journal names that appear in @code{journal} or
@code{journaltitle} fields, and compares them against the second slot
of every triple in @code{org-ref-bibtex-journal-abbreviations}. For
each journal that is missing from that table the package emits a
ready-to-paste @code{add-to-list} form. When network access is
available the package also fetches a CASSI search result page and
fills the third slot with the official Chemical Abstracts Service
abbreviation.


@node Installation
@chapter Installation

@section Manual install

Clone the repository and add it to your @code{load-path}.

@example
git clone https://github.com/MooersLab/sync-journals-bib.git
@end example

Then, in your init file, write the following.

@lisp
(add-to-list 'load-path "~/path/to/sync-journals-bib")
(require 'sync-journals-bib)
@end lisp

@section use-package

@lisp
(use-package sync-journals-bib
  :load-path "~/path/to/sync-journals-bib"
  :commands (sync-journals-bib-sync sync-journals-bib-list-missing))
@end lisp


@node Configuration
@chapter Configuration

The package exposes four customizable variables.

@vtable @code
@item sync-journals-bib-file
Path to the master BibTeX file. The default is
@file{~/Documents/global.bib}.

@item sync-journals-bib-cassi-url
URL of a CASSI search result page. The default points at the URL
supplied by the package author.

@item sync-journals-bib-buffer-name
Name of the output buffer. The default is @samp{*sync-journals-bib*}.

@item sync-journals-bib-fetch-timeout
Number of seconds to wait for the CASSI page to download. The default
is 30.
@end vtable


@node Usage
@chapter Usage

To run the synchronization, call the main command.

@example
M-x sync-journals-bib-sync
@end example

A buffer opens with one @code{add-to-list} form per missing journal.
Copy the forms into your init file, evaluate them, and you are done.

With a prefix argument the command skips the CASSI lookup. This is
useful when working offline.

@example
C-u M-x sync-journals-bib-sync
@end example


@node Commands
@chapter Commands

@deffn Command sync-journals-bib-sync &optional skip-cassi
Generate @code{add-to-list} forms for journals missing from
@code{org-ref-bibtex-journal-abbreviations}. When SKIP-CASSI is
non-nil, the network lookup is skipped.
@end deffn

@deffn Command sync-journals-bib-list-missing
Return the list of journal names found in
@code{sync-journals-bib-file} but absent from
@code{org-ref-bibtex-journal-abbreviations}. Useful from a hook or a
batch script.
@end deffn


@node Functions
@chapter Functions

The internal helpers are documented for completeness. They are not
part of the public API and may change without notice.

@deffn Function sync-journals-bib--journals-in-file bibfile
Return a sorted list of unique journal names found in BIBFILE.
@end deffn

@deffn Function sync-journals-bib--normalize s
Normalize string S for case-insensitive comparison.
@end deffn

@deffn Function sync-journals-bib--known-journals
Return the list of full journal names known to org-ref.
@end deffn

@deffn Function sync-journals-bib--missing-journals &optional bibfile
Return journal names in BIBFILE that are absent from org-ref.
@end deffn

@deffn Function sync-journals-bib--build-snippet full-name &optional cassi-abbrev key
Return a formatted @code{add-to-list} form.
@end deffn

@deffn Function sync-journals-bib--parse-cassi-html html
Return an alist of (FULL-TITLE . CAS-ABBREV) pulled from HTML.
@end deffn


@node Customization
@chapter Customization

Open the customization group with @kbd{M-x customize-group RET
sync-journals-bib RET}. Edit any of the four variables described in
@ref{Configuration}.


@node Testing
@chapter Testing

The package ships with an ERT test suite. From the source directory,
run the following.

@example
make test
@end example

The Makefile launches Emacs in batch mode, loads the library and the
test file, and runs every @code{ert-deftest}.


